1.title: History
1.plot: It's round 10 of the 2010 competition. The Sea Eagles are riding high on the ladder, but will Graham, Coach Des Hasler and his and the clubs stars be able to keep up the momentum? Graham Lowe relives the near death experience that sent him packing from Manly back in 1992. And we get a privileged look inside the inner workings of the NRL judiciary when a reckless tackle sees Steve Matai facing a lengthy ban.

4.title: Next Generation
4.plot: We meet the next generation of Sea Eagles at Manly, in a Toyota Cup side stacked with young Kiwi's. And a young indigenous player's future hangs in the balance as Manly recruitment officer Noel 'Crusher' Cleal makes the tough call on whether or not to sign him to THE CLUB.

5.title: Whanau
5.plot: The Sea Eagles are reeling after a series of defeats and are looking toward this rounds bye reconnect with Whanau and recharge the batteries ready for the next round. Rising star Dean Whare is on a bush hunting trip with his mentor Manly hero Noel 'Crusher' Cleal but has he got the skills to catch a pig?

7.title: Behind the Scenes
7.plot: Losing talented players to season ending injuries is a major threat to the Sea Eagles. Lock Shane Rodney keeps his physio busy, but how do the bone crushing hits on the field compare to his time in the rodeo ring? While the club physio patches up the players, Manly's cheerleading squad 'The Sea Birds' put the finishing touches on their latest routine, which is bound to keep spirits high on the field.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: The Sea Eagles are on the road and heading towards the sunny Gold Coast. An away trip is no holiday though - they're facing a tough game against the Gold Coast Titans on hostile home turf. From the elaborate preparations by the staff to the players themselves the Sea Eagles have to be ready for this tough game.

9.title: The Stadium
9.plot: Every great footie team needs an impressive stadium but the Sea Eagle's home Brookvale Oval could do with some renovations. CEO Graham Lowe has a plan and is applying the pressure to some powerful people during the Federal election.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: It's all happening one night in Manly, The Sea Eagles finals hope rests in winning a bruising battle against the Warriors, while the future of the club could be decided in the Federal election that same evening. Meanwhile, future Manly players are taking part in an indigenous team event out the 'back o' Bourke' watched over by the stars of yesteryear.

imdb.plot outline: He left legendary NRL club the Manly Warringah Sea-Eagles twenty years ago after suffering a massive brain hemorrhage but Kiwi super Coach Graham Lowe has returned, this time as CEO, to finish what he started in a dramatic new series.
